-- Peru Stocks: Cerro Verde, Ferreyros, Milpo, Southern
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-04-09T21:45:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-09/peru-stocks-cerro-verde-ferreyros-milpo-southern.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of the close in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.9 percent to 23,405.64. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  slid 0.7 percent to 2,960.78.  Cia. Minera Milpo (MILPOC1)  (MILPOC1 PE), a silver and zinc producer
controlled by Sao Paulo-based Votorantim Metais Ltda., slumped
2.8 percent to 5.20 soles after silver dropped in  New York .  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for
Caterpillar Inc., fell 2.6 percent to 3 soles after U.S. stocks
declined, said Angel Alcala, a trader at Lima-based Juan Magot y
Asociados SAB.  Casa Grande (CASAGRC1)  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer
and a unit of Gloria SA, slid 2.2 percent to 17.60 soles after
sugar dropped in New York.  Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1)  (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of
Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., fell 2 percent to $41 after
copper declined in New York.  Southern Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), Peru’s largest copper
producer, dropped 1.7 percent to $30.50.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
